summary:
❝It’s too early, Ned❞ 

  The last thing Eddard can feel is the air in his lungs, he can hear Sansa’s scream in his ears,...
caption:
❝It’s too early, Ned❞

The last thing Eddard can feel is the air in his lungs, he can hear Sansa’s scream in his ears, and he can sense the bile in his throat.

The void swallows him into its coils.

He opens his eyes, he puts into focus the myriad of colors of the Godswood and he bats his eyelids.

He spots a feminine figure near the trees.

He moves towards her.

She turns to him, she pulls down her cloak and she looks at him.

“You came back to me too early” Lyanna says to Eddard, “welcome home, Ned” she tells him with a faint smile.

He doesn’t even realize that he’s already shredding tears.

—— Lyanna & Eddard’s reunion in afterlife aesthetic |  © caption by me.

summary: interestingly the unsullied look wholly unprepared for winter. they’re desert dwellers who have never experienced a cold like...
body:
interestingly the unsullied look wholly unprepared for winter. they’re desert dwellers who have never experienced a cold like the northern winters and yet they’re only wearing sleeves (edit they already had sleeves before coming north which is worse) and cloaks. even the dothraki haven’t really bulked up. compare what they are wearing to what wildings wear

i don’t think dany’s might army will be fighting anything other than hypothermia and pneumonia
